Path: This week in Nu #13
Content:
Lucky #13! Welcome to our 13th edition of "This Week in Nu".
We've just begun to create new websites. You can see the early versions live at 
[link: http://www.nushell.sh] www.nushell.sh
 and 
[link: http://blog.nushell.sh] blog.nushell.sh
. If you'd like to help or share your feedback, we'd love to have it! Big thanks to sebastian-xyz for kicking this off!
wycats landed a rewrite of how column-paths work, improved debugging, and added a new 
``what?``
 command to help with debugging commands from inside of Nu (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/986] #986
)
drmason13 has been cleaning up some of our csv/tsv handling logic (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/990] #990
)
jonathandturner added smaller 
``ls``
 and a new 
``ls --full``
 option. As part of this umasks for unix-based were also added (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/979] #979
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/988] #988
)
jonathandturner (building on the work of Southclaws) added support for the 
[link: http://starship.rs] starship.rs
 prompt рџљЂ (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/804] #804
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/970] #970
)
jonathandturner also added support for durations and comparisons with durations (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/978] #978
) and initial support for loading Excel files (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/977] #977
)
Aloso improved how durations were formatted (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/982] #982
)
For folks waiting for homebrew, it's now up to date again! 
[link: https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/nushell] https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/nushell
